{
  "texts": [
    "We trained our model to classify sentences as containing only external content, 50% internal content, 75% internal content, or 100% internal content.",
    "To select classification labels, we calculated the percent of internal content in each sentence in the first dataset we obtained (Devitt & Schacter, 2018; Devitt & Schacter, 2020).",
    "A histogram of these percentages showed clusters at approximately 0, 50, 75, and 100%; hence, our labels.",
    "To identify internal and external information, we used a model designed to be fine-tuned on text for classification.",
    "Specifically, we used distilBERT (Sanh et al., 2019), which is a large language model that can be fine-tuned to new tasks by adding a classification head."
  ]
}